WEBVTT

00:02.850 --> 00:08.737
you're listening to a teaching from Reality LA.

00:08.757 --> 00:11.480
All right, well, last week was Vision Sunday for us.

00:11.580 --> 00:13.923
It was a really big day for us as a church.

00:13.963 --> 00:19.690
We talked about how in 2026, our vision is for everyone to be on mission with Jesus.

00:20.310 --> 00:23.514
And there are three goals that we have throughout this year to come.

00:23.574 --> 00:27.959
And let's engage the essentials, rebuild for renewal, and then share the gospel.

00:28.540 --> 00:30.482
And in terms of the essentials,

00:30.722 --> 00:39.893
There are four essentials for being involved in the church in a healthy way as disciples, and then everything else that we do is recommended for deeper discipleship.

00:40.314 --> 00:51.727
And so here are the four essentials just to remind you of this, to gather on Sundays, to engage the discipleship pathway, to be involved in Christian community, and to serve in some capacity.

00:52.448 --> 01:00.498
And listen, this is not like rules for being a good Christian, and we're not gonna police you on this and shame you if you're not above 75%.

01:00.674 --> 01:06.124
Now, this is just us trying to give clarity on what healthy involvement looks like.

01:06.545 --> 01:14.699
These are not boxes to be checked, they're gifts to be received, and our goal this year is to get as many people doing these four things as we can.

01:14.760 --> 01:24.978
So, before we continue with the book of Acts, we're going to pause that to do a short four-week sermon series on these essentials.

01:25.154 --> 01:33.987
And so today, I'm going to kick it off by preaching on Hebrews chapter 10, verses 19 through 25, and talking about gathering on Sundays.

01:35.189 --> 01:44.342
Now, I want to start off by telling you about a discovery that Harvard's School of Public Health recently made that could have profound implications for human flourishing.

01:45.244 --> 01:55.058
Across multiple large-scale studies, they found that one simple practice is consistently linked with better mental, emotional, and physical health.

01:55.394 --> 02:01.643
One professor even called it a miracle drug because not only is it incredibly healthy for you, it's for free.

02:02.424 --> 02:05.808
And so what is it that the Harvard research discovered?

02:06.469 --> 02:11.997
Well, Tyler Vanderwheel is the director of the Human Flourishing Program at Harvard, and he says this.

02:12.818 --> 02:20.188
The good news is that this miracle drug, regular church attendance, is already in reach of most Americans.

02:20.488 --> 02:24.754
In fact, there's a good chance it's just a short drive away.

02:25.442 --> 02:42.407
That's right, Harvard's School of Public Health has done significant research that shows that regular church attendance is likely to significantly improve your mental, emotional, and even physical health.

02:43.308 --> 02:52.562
And this isn't just talking about being a religious person or this is talking about going to church, being with religious people consistently.

02:52.642 --> 02:55.725
Here's just a sample of the data that they came up with.

02:55.785 --> 02:57.146
I mean, this is legit stuff.

02:57.166 --> 03:01.210
These are like peer-reviewed scholarly articles, all kinds of research.

03:01.310 --> 03:03.473
I mean, Tyler Van Der Wiel leads the whole thing.

03:03.513 --> 03:05.495
He's got degrees from Oxford and Harvard.

03:05.935 --> 03:07.497
But here's some of what they discovered.

03:08.157 --> 03:21.330
Weekly church attendance is associated with a 30% decrease in depression, about an 80% lower risk of suicide, and 33% lower risk of death overall.

03:22.082 --> 03:24.706
And if you don't believe me, look it up.

03:25.246 --> 03:26.768
I mean, it's all there.

03:27.770 --> 03:29.452
You can read the research yourself.

03:29.532 --> 03:30.874
I've read several of the articles.

03:31.395 --> 03:39.246
Or you could read Rebecca McLaughlin's new little book, Summarizing Much of This Research titled, How Church Could Literally Save Your Life.

03:40.167 --> 03:50.962
She says this, study after study has shown that people who attend religious services once a week or more are happier, healthier, and longer lived than those who don't.

03:51.778 --> 03:58.927
Now, of course, this doesn't mean that going to church means that you'll never be depressed, be suicidal, or be sick, okay?

03:59.228 --> 03:59.828
It doesn't mean that.

04:00.389 --> 04:09.501
But it does mean that there are mountains of data showing that you're much less likely to experience those things if you regularly attend church.

04:10.442 --> 04:14.227
Now, the Bible has been saying this for literally thousands of years.

04:14.367 --> 04:16.850
So thank you, Harvard, for noticing it, okay?

04:17.154 --> 04:23.142
But here's the thing, we don't gather primarily for physical or even psychological payoffs.

04:23.743 --> 04:28.790
We gather for worship and to connect with one another as brothers and sisters in Christ.

04:29.711 --> 04:38.783
And we believe that we're whole integrated beings, so it's actually not surprising that what's good for our soul is also good for our mental and physical wellbeing.

04:39.845 --> 04:46.834
But the problem is, is that there are lots of people who call themselves Christians who just don't go to church.

04:47.394 --> 04:53.684
And although there's been a recent uptick, church attendance has been in decline for decades in America.

04:53.725 --> 05:01.057
And more recent studies show that even the average church goer now only goes to church twice a month.

05:02.179 --> 05:06.706
And then, of course, some people say they're Christians and they don't go to church at all.

05:07.266 --> 05:17.598
In fact, one survey showed that only 35% of Americans believe that attending worship services constitutes an essential part of being a Christian.

05:17.618 --> 05:18.339
35%.

05:19.080 --> 05:27.871
That means that 65% think that gathering with the church is unnecessary or optional as followers of Jesus.

05:29.252 --> 05:34.098
Okay, so that's national data on this on church attendance,

05:34.178 --> 05:37.181
How are we doing as a church family on this?

05:37.801 --> 05:44.127
Well, last week we did a survey where we asked, how many times a month you gather with the church?

05:44.147 --> 05:45.609
And so here are the results.

05:46.610 --> 06:01.104
What you'll see here is that 8% said one time per month, 10% said twice a month, 12% said three times a month, and then 70% said that they gather every week unless they're sick or out of town.

06:01.624 --> 06:02.145
Okay, yeah.

06:02.645 --> 06:03.666
It's encouraging.

06:03.938 --> 06:10.426
So, I mean, let me say, first of all, to those 70%, like, man, praise God, that's awesome.

06:10.446 --> 06:10.947
You're doing it.

06:10.967 --> 06:16.834
You're sacrificially committing and gathering with the body of Christ every Sunday.

06:16.874 --> 06:17.474
That's awesome.

06:17.995 --> 06:33.554
And for the 30%, whether you're coming once or twice or three times a month or coming occasionally, I want to invite you today into what Scripture says is a gift of being able to be together with the church and be formed over time in that.

06:34.082 --> 06:45.035
So, I mean, those are kind of the, that was like my initial take on seeing this, but then as I thought about this data more, I realized something because we only did this survey over one Sunday.

06:45.095 --> 06:49.801
We clearly have something going on here called sampling bias, okay?

06:50.281 --> 06:52.124
So here's what I mean, okay?

06:53.265 --> 07:00.914
People who answered once a month, that's probably only one fourth of the people who come once a month, right?

07:01.058 --> 07:06.764
And then people who answered twice a month, we only got half of them to be involved in that survey.

07:06.824 --> 07:12.170
So in other words, our sampling size was skewed towards people who are actually here every week.

07:13.071 --> 07:18.257
So I asked chat GPT to be a statistician for me, okay?

07:19.198 --> 07:30.450
And to weight the data accordingly, and here's what it told me, that basically, that about 50% of the people are here every week, and then 50% come occasionally, 50%.

07:30.882 --> 07:34.066
So this is really important for us.

07:34.968 --> 07:38.833
And let me, I just want to be as clear as I can out the gate on this.

07:39.274 --> 07:42.138
I'm not trying to shame anyone here, okay?

07:42.478 --> 07:44.381
You're here today, praise God.

07:44.421 --> 07:45.883
I'm so grateful that you're here.

07:45.943 --> 07:46.804
You're here, okay?

07:46.824 --> 07:50.510
I'm literally preaching to the choir today about gathering on Sundays, okay?

07:51.371 --> 07:55.316
So I'm not here to shame you, but I am here to invite you into something.

07:55.797 --> 07:57.199
And this is important for us.

07:57.239 --> 07:59.282
And so whether you're here every week,

07:59.362 --> 08:02.306
You show up every once in a while, or this is your first Sunday.

08:02.326 --> 08:08.394
We all need to understand what's so significant about gathering together every Sunday as God's people.

08:08.935 --> 08:14.883
And so to learn about that, we're gonna look at Hebrews chapter 10, verses 19 through 25.

08:15.804 --> 08:19.729
So let me read this passage for us, and then I'll pray that God would speak to us through it.

08:20.851 --> 08:23.895
Hebrews chapter 10, starting in verse 19.

08:26.979 --> 08:29.042
Therefore, brothers, since we have

08:29.410 --> 08:37.586
confidence to enter the holy places by the blood of Jesus, by the new and living way that he opened for us through the curtain that is through his flesh.

08:38.167 --> 08:50.130
And since we have a great priest over the house of God, let us draw near with the true heart and foolish errands of faith, with our hearts sprinkled clean from an evil conscience and our bodies washed with pure water.

08:50.594 --> 08:55.441
Let us hold fast the confession of our hope without wavering, for he who promised his faithful.

08:56.001 --> 09:07.537
And let us consider how to stir up one another to love and good works, not neglecting to meet together as is the habit of some, but encouraging one another and all the more as you see the day drawing near.

09:08.118 --> 09:09.700
This is God's word, pray with me.

09:12.203 --> 09:17.330
God, it is such a privilege for us to be able to come together

09:18.146 --> 09:26.215
to worship you, to hear your word preach, to the receive of the Lord's Supper, to spend time praying, to fellowship.

09:26.275 --> 09:27.737
God, what a privilege.

09:27.837 --> 09:29.179
And we just want to say thank you.

09:29.239 --> 09:36.387
We pray that in this time that you would use your word to help us to see the riches of this and what we have.

09:37.468 --> 09:46.098
Lord, we're mindful of the fact that brothers and sisters in Christ have been doing this for generation after generation.

09:47.074 --> 09:59.251
and that literally right now, and while we were sleeping last night all over the world, Christians were gathering together to worship, to sit under your word, to fellowship.

10:00.233 --> 10:06.041
Some of them, many of them actually, I'm doing that in fear of their life for gathering.

10:06.782 --> 10:12.210
And so we thank you that we have the privilege to be able to do this, God, and we pray today that

10:12.642 --> 10:21.271
that we would be able to understand the significance of what's happening in this moment, but more than understanding it, that we would experience it.

10:21.492 --> 10:22.493
Something special.

10:22.573 --> 10:30.441
Your manifest presence, maybe experience it in a unique and powerful way together.

10:30.462 --> 10:38.691
And then would you help us to be a people who are formed by week in, week out, gathering to worship you?

10:39.011 --> 10:41.874
We pray this all in your son's name, amen.

10:42.434 --> 10:42.855
Amen.

10:43.516 --> 10:49.184
All right, so this is a passage that has a simple but really powerful structure to it.

10:49.284 --> 11:00.941
So what I mean by that is what you have in Hebrews 10 verses 19 through 25 is you have one gospel indicative and then three moral imperatives that follow from that.

11:01.202 --> 11:01.522
Now,

11:01.986 --> 11:07.173
If you slept through English class in high school, let me explain what an indicative and an imperative is, okay?

11:07.693 --> 11:09.716
And to do this in the context of scripture.

11:10.117 --> 11:15.003
An indicative is a declaration of what God has done for you.

11:15.544 --> 11:23.134
It's a type of verb, it's a declaration, whereas an imperative is a command for how you are now called to live.

11:23.915 --> 11:29.682
And the order of how you understand the indicative and imperatives of scripture means everything.

11:30.210 --> 11:34.938
Because every other system in the world says, do this, and then you'll be accepted.

11:35.639 --> 11:38.123
So it leads with imperatives.

11:38.163 --> 11:39.585
You need to do this, you need to do that.

11:39.946 --> 11:42.430
And then maybe God will love you.

11:42.450 --> 11:47.018
And so it's gonna say love other people, and then God will love you.

11:47.098 --> 11:49.762
Be merciful to others, and then God will be merciful to you.

11:50.403 --> 11:55.311
But the gospel says you are accepted, therefore live this way.

11:55.331 --> 11:56.914
It leads

11:57.026 --> 12:03.836
with the indicative, a declaration of what God has done, and then calls us how to live in light of that.

12:03.896 --> 12:08.483
So the gospel says, you are loved, therefore love others.

12:09.264 --> 12:12.890
You are forgiven, therefore forgive others.

12:13.410 --> 12:16.435
I mean, you actually see this structure even in the Ten Commandments.

12:17.056 --> 12:18.578
The beginning of the Ten Commandments

12:19.010 --> 12:26.801
If you go back to Exodus chapter 20 is where it says, God says, I'm the Lord your God who brought you out of slavery in Egypt.

12:26.841 --> 12:27.803
That's the indicative.

12:28.403 --> 12:29.345
I've redeemed you.

12:29.385 --> 12:33.751
Therefore, and then he gives 10 moral imperatives, commands.

12:34.372 --> 12:38.238
Therefore, this is how you live in light of what I've done for you.

12:38.878 --> 12:44.146
So that's going to change the entire way that you think about Christianity and read the Bible.

12:44.354 --> 12:51.681
Some of you came in here today thinking, it's commands, and if I obey those commands, then God loves me and maybe will save me.

12:52.081 --> 12:53.403
And I'm saying, it's the opposite.

12:53.983 --> 12:54.844
It's gospel.

12:54.984 --> 12:55.785
God loves you.

12:55.965 --> 12:56.726
He's for you.

12:56.906 --> 12:58.247
He saves you by grace.

12:58.548 --> 13:00.249
And then he gives us commands.

13:01.290 --> 13:04.693
So that's what's going on here in Hebrews chapter 10.

13:04.753 --> 13:13.682
We have one major indicative, this gospel declaration upfront, and then three imperatives that flow from it about how we live.

13:14.178 --> 13:16.862
So first of all, let's look at the gospel indicative.

13:16.922 --> 13:18.784
This is in verses 19 through 21.

13:19.806 --> 13:39.652
Says, therefore brothers, reminding us here that we're talking about the church as family, therefore brothers, since we have confidence to enter into the holy places by the blood of Jesus, by the new and living way that he opened for us through the curtain that is through his flesh, and since we have a great priest over the house of God.

13:39.912 --> 13:41.074
So pause right there.

13:41.186 --> 13:42.630
That's the indicative.

13:42.650 --> 13:52.715
The declaration here is that the blood of Jesus was shed on your behalf so that you can enter into God's presence, not with fear, but with confidence.

13:53.517 --> 13:54.259
It's beautiful.

13:54.881 --> 13:58.610
This means that your greatest problem has already been solved.

13:59.010 --> 14:11.432
I mean, I know that we all have problems in our lives and you're worrying about stuff and maybe you don't know how you're going to pay rent or how you're going to deal with this situation at work or you've got this relationship or you've got a physical ailment, like we've all got problems in our lives.

14:11.472 --> 14:17.202
But this declaration is saying sin is our greatest problem and your greatest problem has already been solved.

14:17.858 --> 14:24.488
because Jesus has dealt with it by going to the cross in our place, bearing our sin.

14:24.548 --> 14:31.459
This is a declaration that by the grace of God and his son Jesus, that we are reconciled to God.

14:32.441 --> 14:37.008
And if you read this in the context of the book of Hebrews, this is the theological summit.

14:37.528 --> 14:43.698
Everything the author has been arguing leads here that Jesus has offered the final sacrifice.

14:44.034 --> 14:49.800
He's opened the way and secured our reconciliation once and for all.

14:50.221 --> 14:51.583
It is finished.

14:51.963 --> 14:56.108
That is the one indicative, this declaration of good news.

14:57.209 --> 15:01.133
And then from it, flow three imperatives.

15:01.854 --> 15:03.756
But before we get to those imperatives, you got that?

15:03.876 --> 15:06.559
I mean, please, you can't skip over that.

15:06.579 --> 15:07.781
I'm like, yeah, but tell me what to do.

15:08.462 --> 15:09.162
Like, no, no, no, no.

15:09.503 --> 15:12.466
That's not how we do things.

15:12.610 --> 15:14.393
Okay, like you need to do this.

15:14.513 --> 15:16.436
You need to obey these rules.

15:17.077 --> 15:19.220
No, we understand the gospel.

15:19.280 --> 15:20.362
We understand it in our heads.

15:20.422 --> 15:25.670
It grips our hearts and then it shapes every aspect of our lives.

15:25.690 --> 15:36.146
So from this gospel indicative, you have these three imperatives and the structure is actually really obvious in the text because each one of these starts with the phrase let us.

15:36.482 --> 15:49.803
So in verse 22, let us, in verse 23, let us in 24, let us, all of this we're doing in light of the fact that Jesus has shed his blood and made a way for us to enter into the presence of God.

15:50.585 --> 15:56.614
So three imperatives that flow from the gospel, the first in verse 22 is, let us draw near to God.

15:57.456 --> 16:01.362
Look with me at verse 22, it says, let us draw near,

16:01.506 --> 16:10.600
with a true heart and full assurance of faith, with our hearts sprinkled clean from an evil conscience, and our bodies washed with pure water.

16:11.221 --> 16:21.939
So, I mean, this is all building on this gospel declaration, you've been washed, you've been given a new heart, and God has drawn near to you.

16:21.959 --> 16:26.165
And so our response is, let us draw near to him.

16:26.225 --> 16:29.170
Let us realize that this

16:29.282 --> 16:31.524
that He is our greatest good.

16:31.585 --> 16:34.788
There's nothing better than being in the presence of God.

16:34.808 --> 16:40.975
There's nothing better than being in relationship with God, where you know Him and He knows you.

16:41.035 --> 16:45.380
You know that you're never alone because He's always right there.

16:46.601 --> 16:51.887
But I want you to notice that it's saying that we need each other to draw near to God.

16:53.028 --> 16:54.450
See, your temptation would be

16:54.530 --> 17:01.697
Let us draw near to God and for you to think that it's just talking about all of us as individuals, maybe doing that at the same time.

17:03.098 --> 17:05.160
But no, this is communal to the core.

17:05.921 --> 17:08.883
We need each other to draw near to God.

17:10.025 --> 17:13.888
And so there are weeks when your faith feels strong and there are weeks when it doesn't.

17:14.949 --> 17:18.452
And in those moments, you don't just need to draw near to God yourself.

17:19.313 --> 17:24.338
You need to draw near by sitting next to someone who's still singing when you don't feel like singing.

17:25.058 --> 17:28.662
You draw near by hearing someone else pray when you don't have the words.

17:29.263 --> 17:34.309
You draw near by watching someone else hold on to hope when you feel like yours is thin.

17:35.571 --> 17:38.094
Let us draw near to God.

17:38.875 --> 17:43.761
That's the first imperative based on this good news that's declared.

17:43.801 --> 17:47.666
The second is this, let us hold fast to the end.

17:48.258 --> 17:56.290
Look at verse 23, let us hold fast the confession of our hope without wavering for he who promised is faithful.

17:57.913 --> 18:02.380
So the book of Hebrews is actually written to a group of people who are on the verge of giving up.

18:03.321 --> 18:10.793
They were wavering in their faith, their grip was loosening on hope, and many were drifting from Jesus and the church.

18:11.634 --> 18:15.120
And God's word for them is to hold fast.

18:15.741 --> 18:16.722
Don't let go.

18:16.930 --> 18:17.691
Don't give up.

18:17.952 --> 18:20.375
Indoor faithfully to the end.

18:20.415 --> 18:23.260
And that's God's word for us today.

18:23.280 --> 18:25.783
I know that some of you are weary.

18:25.823 --> 18:27.746
Some of you are wavering.

18:27.786 --> 18:31.292
Some of you right now are on the verge of giving up.

18:31.472 --> 18:32.654
And I want to plead with you.

18:33.014 --> 18:34.256
Look to Christ.

18:34.657 --> 18:35.899
Hold fast to Him.

18:35.939 --> 18:37.421
Don't give up.

18:37.441 --> 18:39.744
Persevere until the end.

18:39.784 --> 18:44.511
But you're not going to be able to do this based on your own strength.

18:45.353 --> 18:46.194
Remember,

18:46.338 --> 18:50.164
a command that's based on the declaration of what God has done for us.

18:50.244 --> 18:56.414
And he reminds us of that in verse 23, let us hold fast the confession of our hope without wavering.

18:56.474 --> 18:56.754
Why?

18:56.774 --> 18:59.819
For he who promised is faithful.

19:01.362 --> 19:06.890
Your endurance will not be because of your faithfulness, but because of his faithfulness in your life.

19:08.172 --> 19:14.322
And you're going to persevere, not by looking within, but by looking to him, the faithful one.

19:15.010 --> 19:20.276
He is the one who started a good work in you and who will bring it to completion.

19:21.017 --> 19:22.358
And so hold fast.

19:23.360 --> 19:27.624
But once again, it doesn't just say, hey, individual, hold fast.

19:28.686 --> 19:31.309
He says, Christ has opened the way for us.

19:31.969 --> 19:35.053
Let us hold fast to the end.

19:35.073 --> 19:37.135
Once again, this is communal.

19:37.816 --> 19:41.661
We need each other to persevere until the end.

19:42.141 --> 19:42.962
We need each other.

19:43.458 --> 19:45.562
You can't stray away from the group.

19:45.602 --> 19:47.085
That's when you will start to wither.

19:48.748 --> 19:56.263
In fact, I think about when our kids are a little bit younger, we used to watch all the planet Earth episodes that were out.

19:56.303 --> 19:59.409
There's never ending planet Earth series.

20:00.831 --> 20:02.334
We would watch those because the kids loved it.

20:02.354 --> 20:04.338
We loved it.

20:04.482 --> 20:10.291
There's a pattern that I noticed that kind of surprised me in watching how animals work.

20:10.852 --> 20:21.929
And it is that I thought that when you would have a fight between two animals, that you would have the strongest lion of the pack and the strongest wildebeest of their pack.

20:22.470 --> 20:25.414
And they would fight and the lion would win, of course, because he's the king.

20:26.897 --> 20:29.381
But actually, it really doesn't work that way at all.

20:29.701 --> 20:32.946
And I remember watching Planet Earth.

20:33.090 --> 20:34.194
some scene like this.

20:34.274 --> 20:36.743
It's like, oh, look at that wildebeest.

20:38.269 --> 20:39.112
Oh, he's limping.

20:39.172 --> 20:40.698
Poor thing.

20:40.758 --> 20:42.303
He's got a hurt leg, but that's okay.

20:42.324 --> 20:43.126
He's with a pack.

20:43.207 --> 20:45.234
They're like surrounding him, right?

20:45.378 --> 20:47.461
And you're like, and then the lions come.

20:47.501 --> 20:50.164
And it's not the male lions, they're sleeping under a tree.

20:50.224 --> 20:52.247
The female lions go hunting.

20:52.267 --> 20:56.472
And no, the female lions, they don't go and find the strongest wildebeest.

20:56.492 --> 20:58.274
Like, let's get some honor out of this kill.

20:58.334 --> 20:59.456
Like, no, what do they do?

20:59.476 --> 21:02.980
They scare the wildebeest and they all start to run off.

21:03.000 --> 21:06.024
And they look for the one that's limping who goes off on the side.

21:06.044 --> 21:08.107
And I'm watching with this with my kids.

21:08.127 --> 21:09.709
They think the world is a great place.

21:10.450 --> 21:13.714
And then all of a sudden it's like, why are they going for the one that's limping?

21:13.794 --> 21:18.599
And before you know it, this pack of lions is just ripping this wounded wildebeest into pieces.

21:18.639 --> 21:20.902
And my kids are crying, right?

21:21.823 --> 21:23.445
And this isn't just a one-time thing.

21:23.505 --> 21:26.408
It's like the next scene is like, look at that pack of elephants.

21:26.909 --> 21:28.430
Oh, look at the baby.

21:28.470 --> 21:29.832
It's so cute.

21:30.192 --> 21:31.934
And then it's like, you see it happening.

21:31.954 --> 21:32.835
You're like, no, no, no.

21:33.096 --> 21:34.898
Baby, I don't stray from the pack.

21:35.238 --> 21:36.339
You've got to stray from the pack.

21:36.359 --> 21:38.261
And then they go for the baby every time, right?

21:38.622 --> 21:40.564
So here I tell you the story for this reason.

21:40.764 --> 21:42.386
You can't stray from the pack.

21:43.010 --> 21:48.116
If you want to endure till the end, you've got to stay with the pack.

21:49.137 --> 21:55.203
Some of you are really young in your faith and you need to stick with older brothers and sisters in Christ.

21:55.223 --> 21:57.746
You need spiritual mothers and fathers in your life.

21:57.766 --> 21:58.927
You've got to stay with the pack.

21:59.408 --> 22:00.789
Some of you are wounded right now.

22:00.809 --> 22:06.896
You're hurting and you think, I'm just going to go off on my own for a little bit and try and heal myself up so I can get back.

22:06.916 --> 22:08.818
You've got to stay with the pack.

22:08.898 --> 22:11.863
This is the only way that we are going to endure to the end.

22:11.923 --> 22:16.250
That's why it says, let us hold fast to the end.

22:17.392 --> 22:25.545
All right, the third command then that it's gonna give us based on this gospel declaration is let us stir up one another to love.

22:26.506 --> 22:27.428
Look at verse 24.

22:27.448 --> 22:32.836
It says, and let us consider how to stir up one another to love and good works.

22:33.638 --> 22:36.402
I just love this imagery of stirring up.

22:36.578 --> 22:42.407
beautiful imagery of what it looks like for us to be a loving community.

22:42.427 --> 22:49.057
And just imagine with me for a moment that I had a big bag of cement powder right here.

22:49.097 --> 22:52.522
And then I had a big bucket of water right here.

22:52.562 --> 22:57.770
Now, with those two things separate, they're completely useless, okay?

22:58.110 --> 23:00.133
Big bag of cement powder, water.

23:00.153 --> 23:02.377
I mean, they're not helping much on their own.

23:03.098 --> 23:06.002
But if you mix them together,

23:06.658 --> 23:08.580
then something amazing starts to happen.

23:08.600 --> 23:18.052
If you mix them together and you start to stir them up, you literally have chemical reactions that are taking place that are creating new bonds.

23:18.352 --> 23:29.005
And in fact, what happens is it creates something altogether new since they've been stirred up and it creates something that's cohesive and useful and helpful.

23:29.887 --> 23:32.690
Well, that's exactly how love works.

23:33.090 --> 23:36.677
You've got some people here, and you've got some people there.

23:37.739 --> 23:52.307
But when we come together, love catalyzes good works, stirs us up, and we become a part of something, a community that's far greater, where the sum is far greater than just the total of the parts.

23:53.389 --> 23:56.274
It's like there are chemical reactions happening.

23:56.418 --> 24:02.564
when we serve each other, when we encourage each other, when we speak the truth to one another, when we pray for one another.

24:02.824 --> 24:07.028
And all of that binds us together stronger than cement.

24:08.189 --> 24:10.011
And so you need each other.

24:10.031 --> 24:13.614
You need the people who are sitting around you right now.

24:13.674 --> 24:18.979
You need others in your life who will stir you up to love and good works.

24:18.999 --> 24:23.123
And you need to stir up others to love and good works as well.

24:23.364 --> 24:25.906
You can't do this on your own.

24:27.714 --> 24:31.218
And so let me just review what we've seen in this passage.

24:31.238 --> 24:38.686
You have this gospel indicative, a declaration of what God has done for us in Christ because his blood was shed on the cross.

24:39.066 --> 24:45.033
The way has been opened and we can enter into the throne room of God, not with fear, but with confidence.

24:45.874 --> 24:53.362
And then based on this gospel declaration, we have three imperatives, three commands.

24:53.570 --> 24:57.457
These commands flow from this new reality of being in Christ.

24:57.798 --> 24:59.401
Let us draw near to God.

24:59.742 --> 25:01.305
Let us hold fast to the end.

25:01.666 --> 25:04.190
Let us stir up one another to love.

25:05.453 --> 25:09.761
But if we keep reading, there's one thing that it says not to do.

25:10.723 --> 25:12.306
So we've got the gospel.

25:12.898 --> 25:19.825
We've got three commands of things that we ought to do in light of the gospel, but then one thing that it says absolutely don't do this.

25:19.905 --> 25:20.746
And so what is it?

25:20.806 --> 25:31.478
It must be really important if there's only one thing that it says not to do while we read in verse 25, not neglecting to meet together as is the habit of son.

25:32.979 --> 25:39.506
Now, there are a variety of ways that we meet together as Christians, but the heart of that is gathering on Sundays.

25:40.130 --> 25:48.438
And so I wanna zoom in on this phrase, meet together and unpack the significance of the Sunday gathering.

25:49.439 --> 25:50.300
What's going on here?

25:50.360 --> 25:54.204
What's happening when we come together on Sundays for worship?

25:54.945 --> 26:00.691
Well, the word in the original Greek here for meet together literally means to assemble.

26:01.592 --> 26:02.433
We're in assembly.

26:02.913 --> 26:07.858
So we don't use the word assembly too often, you might think about it in a school context.

26:07.938 --> 26:14.787
where everyone's off in their own classrooms doing their different things, but when they have an assembly, they all come together.

26:15.789 --> 26:17.511
Or here's another way that you could think about this.

26:18.092 --> 26:22.558
Imagine a bicycle that's disassembled, okay?

26:22.959 --> 26:30.028
So if you have a bike that's disassembled, you have all the different parts, like imagine a pile of bike parts.

26:30.849 --> 26:37.138
You've got the tire and then you've got some spokes and some pedals and there's the handlebars and the chain.

26:37.410 --> 26:39.694
the seat, but it's all just a pile.

26:39.714 --> 26:43.481
And because it's disassembled, it's not useful.

26:43.561 --> 26:44.523
It's not functioning.

26:44.543 --> 26:47.188
It's not doing what it was meant to do.

26:47.208 --> 26:57.426
But when the bike is assembled, when everything comes together and functions in its proper role and its relation to everything else, then the bike can do what it's meant to do.

26:58.338 --> 27:09.997
Well, when we assemble as the church on Sundays, it's a time for us to come together in all of our differences, our gifts, our experiences, our backgrounds, and to rejoice in our unity in Christ.

27:10.798 --> 27:13.783
With one voice, we exalt Christ in song.

27:14.343 --> 27:21.295
As one people, we sit under the authority of God's word, and as one family, we receive the Lord's Supper together.

27:22.657 --> 27:26.002
And technically speaking, we don't go to church,

27:26.274 --> 27:30.640
we are the church and we gather for worship on Sundays.

27:31.702 --> 27:36.008
So the church is not an event or a place, the church is a family.

27:36.709 --> 27:39.954
In fact, here's my one sentence definition of the church.

27:40.535 --> 27:50.770
The church is a family of sinners who are being redeemed by grace, who are led by qualified leaders, who gather for worship and scatter for mission to the glory of God.

27:51.471 --> 27:53.554
That's what a church is.

27:53.762 --> 27:58.128
And so gathering isn't just something that we do, it's at the heart of who we are.

27:59.710 --> 28:11.404
So if that's what church is, not an event, not a place, but a family gathered by grace, then the question becomes, what should our gatherings actually be like?

28:12.746 --> 28:15.890
What should mark us when we come together on Sundays?

28:16.514 --> 28:21.561
Well, I wanna show you based on scripture, seven characteristics of the Sunday gathering.

28:21.701 --> 28:30.013
These are seven marks of a Sunday gathering in the New Testament church that I think can shape us right here in Los Angeles.

28:30.033 --> 28:30.774
And I wanna do this.

28:31.374 --> 28:37.543
So like it says in Hebrews 1025 that we can not give up meeting together as some are in the habit of doing.

28:37.583 --> 28:41.829
So first, the Sunday gathering is sacred.

28:42.270 --> 28:42.770
Sacred.

28:43.972 --> 28:45.554
When the Bible talks about

28:45.922 --> 28:50.487
God's people gathering, it assumes that something extraordinary is happening.

28:51.028 --> 28:54.812
God is present with His people and in a unique way.

28:54.832 --> 29:04.343
I mean, God's present everywhere and He's with us all the time, but when we gather on Sundays together, He's with us in a unique and powerful way.

29:04.383 --> 29:10.871
And this right here is not just a group of people choosing to be in the same room at the same time.

29:10.931 --> 29:13.874
This is a people being summoned by God.

29:14.530 --> 29:18.356
And what makes this gathering different is not the music, the message, or the mood.

29:18.436 --> 29:19.678
It's the presence of God.

29:20.960 --> 29:26.128
So if what you want is the buzz of a crowd, you can go to a Kendrick Lamar concert.

29:27.089 --> 29:30.334
If you're looking for wisdom, you can go to a lecture at Caltech.

29:30.354 --> 29:33.459
If you want to discover yourself, you can go on a retreat into Panga.

29:34.520 --> 29:37.785
If you want community, you can find it on apps like Meetup.

29:38.587 --> 29:39.828
All of those things have their place.

29:40.489 --> 29:43.474
But what we experience here is something different.

29:44.002 --> 29:46.064
This is not just collective energy.

29:46.144 --> 29:48.006
It's the fellowship of the Holy Spirit.

29:48.787 --> 29:50.149
This is not just insight.

29:50.229 --> 29:51.570
It's divine encounter.

29:51.630 --> 29:53.312
This is not entertainment.

29:53.372 --> 29:54.193
It's worship.

29:54.653 --> 29:56.716
This is not just social connection.

29:56.776 --> 29:57.577
It's communion.

29:58.337 --> 30:00.039
We're not just exchanging ideas.

30:00.099 --> 30:02.462
We're coming into the presence of a living God.

30:02.902 --> 30:11.392
This gathering is sacred, not because of the building or the people, but because God has promised to meet with His people when they assemble in His name.

30:11.472 --> 30:11.792
Amen?

30:12.513 --> 30:13.714
This gathering is sacred.

30:15.266 --> 30:17.589
So next, the Sunday gathering is communal.

30:18.811 --> 30:21.475
We are not alone and this reminds us of that.

30:22.797 --> 30:29.667
And we need to understand this because for us oftentimes our default is individual private spirituality.

30:30.588 --> 30:38.640
And then we think of the church as something that we tack on to our individual private spirituality to kind of help us be more well-rounded.

30:39.581 --> 30:42.706
And so it's easy for us to think of the Sunday gathering in that sense.

30:43.170 --> 30:47.254
But what we learn in the scriptures is that the order is actually the opposite.

30:47.835 --> 30:54.502
The core of who we are is that we are a family of God, brothers and sisters in Christ.

30:54.702 --> 30:57.105
Our core identity is communal.

30:57.926 --> 31:01.990
And then how we understand our individual spirituality flows from that.

31:02.791 --> 31:09.298
And so when we gather on Sundays, this just isn't another event that you add on to your individual week.

31:09.666 --> 31:13.071
This is the fountainhead from which everything else flows.

31:13.893 --> 31:15.595
We proclaim the gospel.

31:15.876 --> 31:23.167
We respond in worship and rejoicing in the glory of God at the top of our lungs in the heart of this city.

31:23.187 --> 31:31.239
And then everything flows out of that place of we are a people who have been called to God and who worship God.

31:32.021 --> 31:35.506
And so this is all deeply communal.

31:35.842 --> 31:38.966
And the gathering is not individuals who come to watch a service.

31:39.406 --> 31:41.969
It's a family who bring an offering to God.

31:43.110 --> 31:45.854
Next, the Sunday gathering is embodied.

31:47.055 --> 31:49.578
We gather to meet face to face.

31:50.078 --> 31:54.283
Now, in the New Testament, obviously they met in person.

31:54.343 --> 31:56.666
They didn't have digital options for that.

31:58.028 --> 32:03.634
But that's not the only basis of the argument of the embodied nature

32:03.746 --> 32:06.229
of the gathering of the church and the New Testament.

32:06.289 --> 32:11.416
I mean, what you see happening in the church gathering is receiving of the Lord's Supper.

32:11.436 --> 32:13.940
I mean, that's at the heart of the gathering.

32:13.960 --> 32:19.287
There's nothing more tangible, something that engages your taste and your smell and your touch.

32:19.807 --> 32:21.309
And we do that together.

32:21.390 --> 32:24.754
And it's not only the Lord's Supper, it's greeting one another.

32:25.442 --> 32:32.569
For them, it was a holy kiss for us as a handshake, fist bump, a hug, whatever appropriate way it is to greet one another.

32:32.609 --> 32:35.712
Physical touch is important for that.

32:35.732 --> 32:43.679
But when we come together, our voices join together to make something that's different, all combined, and we would be separately.

32:44.700 --> 32:55.410
And so in our disembodied age, we need to embrace the embodied communal spirituality that God has called us to.

32:56.098 --> 32:59.302
We do have a live stream, but I wanna be clear.

32:59.362 --> 33:02.487
You can't gather with the church online.

33:03.528 --> 33:07.854
You can watch a gathering online, but that's different.

33:07.874 --> 33:11.939
You can't participate in it the way you can when you're here in person.

33:12.620 --> 33:16.445
And listen, there are valid reasons for using the live stream.

33:16.485 --> 33:21.952
If you're sick, if you're traveling, if you've taken care of sick kids at home, anything like that.

33:22.693 --> 33:26.098
But otherwise, our hope is that we would gather

33:26.370 --> 33:28.893
together, communally embodied.

33:29.755 --> 33:31.157
You don't just need content.

33:31.217 --> 33:32.338
You need connection.

33:32.378 --> 33:37.946
And the live stream is not a replacement for in-person church.

33:38.647 --> 33:43.334
It's a supplement that's meant for people who are sick or traveling or they're shut-ins.

33:43.394 --> 33:47.900
And so, man, if you're watching on the live stream right now, we love you.

33:47.920 --> 33:52.466
I just want to extend an invitation for you to gather on Sundays.

33:52.887 --> 33:55.250
We need you here and you need us.

33:56.130 --> 33:59.113
And I want to say that, again, I'm not trying to shame anyone.

33:59.173 --> 34:01.736
Some of you might be listening and thinking, yeah, but what about this?

34:01.776 --> 34:02.997
Or what about my situation there?

34:03.018 --> 34:05.180
Or I've got these things from the past.

34:05.620 --> 34:07.302
We would just love to talk to you about that too.

34:08.584 --> 34:11.226
We don't want you to be separated.

34:11.567 --> 34:16.953
So consider the embodied nature of the Sunday gathering.

34:17.894 --> 34:20.517
Next, the Sunday gathering is participatory.

34:21.838 --> 34:24.281
Church is not a performance to watch.

34:25.122 --> 34:25.522
It's not.

34:26.082 --> 34:37.136
Colossians 3.16, it says, let the word of Christ dwell in you richly teaching and admonishing one another, Psalms and hymns and spiritual songs.

34:37.436 --> 34:41.120
It's this picture of gathering together and we're bringing something.

34:41.861 --> 34:42.943
We're contributing.

34:43.043 --> 34:45.085
We give and we receive.

34:46.467 --> 34:55.378
I think one of the problems with the way that people engage with church and with Sunday gatherings today is that consumerism has deeply plagued the church.

34:56.226 --> 35:02.976
People come to church like customers consuming a product and then leave the review on Yelp afterwards.

35:04.018 --> 35:07.082
And listen, there's a place for feedback, okay?

35:07.763 --> 35:14.774
But what I hope for people is that they come with a mindset of I'm not a spectator, I'm a participant.

35:16.236 --> 35:23.607
I'm a family member who's gathering with my family to praise our father and to encourage one another.

35:23.627 --> 35:25.490
You're not a consumer.

35:25.634 --> 35:26.696
You're a contributor.

35:26.716 --> 35:28.358
That's what it means to be a disciple.

35:29.400 --> 35:31.864
Next, the Sunday gathering is consistent.

35:32.364 --> 35:35.429
So you see this develop throughout the scriptures.

35:35.529 --> 35:38.834
In the Old Testament, there's a pattern of God's people coming together.

35:38.874 --> 35:44.443
In between the Old Testament and the New Testament, you have something called the synagogue that developed.

35:45.084 --> 35:46.967
They had this because they didn't have the temple.

35:47.387 --> 35:51.794
And so they would come together and they would read scripture and they would teach on it and they would worship.

35:52.258 --> 35:57.843
That really formed the basis of what would start happening in the gatherings of the church and the New Testament.

35:58.404 --> 36:06.392
But what you see in the New Testament, and especially throughout the book of Acts, is it talks about the church gathering on the Lord's day as the first day of the week.

36:06.932 --> 36:12.498
So this goes all the way back to Jesus rises on Sunday, and then he meets with his gathered disciples.

36:12.878 --> 36:14.340
Pentecost happens on a Sunday.

36:14.420 --> 36:16.722
The spirit falls on his gathered disciples.

36:17.363 --> 36:20.946
And then throughout Acts, the church begins to gather on Sundays.

36:21.506 --> 36:23.668
And Sunday was not the Sabbath.

36:24.509 --> 36:27.112
The Sabbath was from Friday night to Saturday night.

36:27.833 --> 36:32.678
The church started gathering on Sundays because that's the day that Jesus rose from the dead.

36:33.499 --> 36:43.150
They would gather to worship the resurrected Christ, to remember what He's done for them, and to dwell in His presence by the Spirit.

36:44.011 --> 36:46.994
And so the point is that throughout the New Testament,

36:47.202 --> 36:52.549
They didn't gather for worship when they felt like it or when they felt they needed it or they didn't have anything else going on.

36:53.190 --> 36:57.396
They gathered every Sunday on the Lord's day because that's what God called them to do.

36:58.237 --> 37:02.222
So we establish a rhythm with the consistency of it.

37:02.703 --> 37:05.627
Next, the Sunday gathering is formation.

37:06.248 --> 37:07.249
This is so important.

37:07.309 --> 37:14.859
I mean, in Hebrews 10, 25, it says, let us not give up meeting together as is the habit of some.

37:15.600 --> 37:16.882
So habits,

37:17.026 --> 37:20.550
are really important in shaping your character and your soul.

37:21.431 --> 37:33.184
And our character is shaped the most in life, not by the big out-of-the-norm events, but rather by the things that we do repeatedly day in, day out, week by week.

37:33.204 --> 37:37.449
You could learn that from Aristotle, or you could learn it from James Clear's atomic habits.

37:37.689 --> 37:39.892
It's January, so I'm assuming some of you just read it.

37:40.292 --> 37:41.393
Great book.

37:41.413 --> 37:45.618
But what you're gonna learn from those is that your habits form your loves.

37:46.306 --> 37:52.798
The little thing is that you do repeatedly in your life or what's going to shape you as a person overall.

37:53.660 --> 38:00.673
And so when it comes to church, it's not the one epic church service here or there that will shape you the most.

38:01.054 --> 38:07.666
It's the week to week gathering with the saints that will form your heart and your character over time.

38:08.194 --> 38:11.337
It's not only about gathering with the church every week.

38:11.357 --> 38:24.792
I mean, that's my hope is that you have a long-term vision of discipleship where you're being conformed into the image of Jesus, and you see that gathering with the church on Sundays is a key part of shaping you over decades with that.

38:25.773 --> 38:33.682
Every week, it's chiseling away your sinful nature and conforming you more and more to the image of Christ.

38:33.986 --> 38:39.533
It's not only just about coming to church, it's about what we do every Sunday in these gatherings.

38:40.114 --> 38:45.041
So every element of our gatherings is meant to form us as disciples of Jesus.

38:45.902 --> 38:49.987
The call to worship reminds us that God initiates the relationship and we respond.

38:50.889 --> 38:54.754
The public reading of scripture trains us to listen to God's voice above all.

38:55.595 --> 38:58.839
Prayer teaches us dependence, not self-sufficiency.

38:59.460 --> 39:03.826
The offering loosens our grip on money and retrains our trust in God.

39:04.482 --> 39:12.209
Passing the peace or the meet and greet, as we often call it, forms us into a reconciled people, not just spiritual individuals.

39:12.950 --> 39:17.434
The preached word re-orients us around God's truth, not the stories of this world.

39:18.455 --> 39:21.959
Communion reminds us that we live by grace, not by earning.

39:22.779 --> 39:27.644
And corporate worship shapes our loves, teaching us what is truly worthy of praise.

39:28.585 --> 39:33.810
And then lastly, the benediction sends us out with God's presence, not just with good intentions.

39:34.722 --> 39:42.975
And so Sundays are a key part of your discipleship, the way that you are becoming more and more like Jesus over time.

39:44.237 --> 39:47.342
And then lastly, the Sunday gathering is missional.

39:48.083 --> 39:52.230
So we don't gather on Sundays to avoid mission.

39:53.071 --> 39:59.261
Our goal is not to be an insular community that comes together and builds walls and never goes out and engages with the world.

39:59.702 --> 40:02.546
No, remember what I said, what it means to be the church?

40:02.754 --> 40:05.697
We gather for worship and we scatter for mission.

40:06.458 --> 40:10.703
So we gather, but then we gather to be sent out.

40:12.004 --> 40:14.087
I love the way that Leslie New began to put it.

40:15.488 --> 40:26.621
The church is not meant to call men and women out of the world into a safe religious enclave, but to call them out in order to send them back as agents of God's kingship.

40:26.641 --> 40:27.342
I love that.

40:27.982 --> 40:29.044
We gather together.

40:30.165 --> 40:31.186
It forms us.

40:31.394 --> 40:35.559
It trains our hearts, and then we are sent out a salt and light in this world.

40:36.600 --> 40:42.888
And if you gather, but you don't scatter, then you would just be an exclusive community, or an exclusive community.

40:43.068 --> 40:50.577
If you gather and you don't scatter, we become self-absorbed, blind to the brokenness around us, and we wouldn't fulfill Jesus' call to go to the nations.

40:51.498 --> 40:56.024
But if you scatter and you don't gather, then you would be a fragmented movement.

40:56.565 --> 40:57.746
We would lose our center,

40:58.082 --> 41:03.611
We would no longer have a community to invite others into, and we'd become isolated and burned out.

41:03.631 --> 41:08.578
When we gather and we scatter, we are a family on mission with Jesus.

41:09.379 --> 41:10.381
That's what the church is.

41:11.322 --> 41:17.692
And when we are rooted in the church, then we could branch out in seeking the flourishing of our city.

41:18.794 --> 41:22.960
So these are seven characteristics of the Sunday gathering.

41:23.221 --> 41:26.546
And this should go without saying, but let me just

41:26.754 --> 41:33.904
Say it explicitly, is that the Sunday gathering is an important part of the Christian life, but it is not the whole of the Christian life.

41:34.645 --> 41:38.491
I'm emphasizing it today because that's what I'm preaching on, okay?

41:38.972 --> 41:42.277
And there are some Christians who are like Sunday only Christians.

41:42.597 --> 41:47.845
They're like amening everything I'm saying right now, and then they don't do anything for Jesus throughout the week, okay?

41:48.345 --> 41:54.354
So we don't wanna be Sunday only Christians, but we also don't wanna be no Sunday Christians.

41:54.754 --> 41:56.156
was like, yeah, I just follow Jesus.

41:56.236 --> 41:59.540
I just, you know, me and God, I got in nature.

41:59.560 --> 42:00.281
I don't need the church.

42:00.321 --> 42:03.826
Like, well, the problem is Jesus is telling you that you need the church.

42:04.206 --> 42:08.372
So if you say you only need Jesus, then you're going to end up needing the church as well.

42:09.113 --> 42:11.396
So we don't want to be Sunday only Christians.

42:11.516 --> 42:13.398
We don't want to be no Sunday Christians.

42:13.418 --> 42:19.346
We want to be faithful Christians who gather on Sundays, that's a fountainhead, and then we live out

42:19.970 --> 42:25.097
of the beautiful truths that we're celebrating here together on Sundays.

42:25.878 --> 42:37.353
Now, I just want to give you three practical invitations here because I've been laying out the significance and the meaning of the Sunday gathering.

42:37.474 --> 42:38.755
Three really practical things.

42:39.096 --> 42:46.706
One is to gather on Sundays every week, to commit to that, to prioritize it, to plan things around it.

42:47.138 --> 42:50.403
to say, I'm going to come when I feel like it and I'm going to come when I don't feel like it.

42:50.543 --> 42:51.905
So that's the first.

42:51.965 --> 42:53.788
It's just gather on Sundays every week.

42:54.349 --> 42:58.054
Second is, come not as a consumer but as a family member.

42:59.096 --> 43:02.240
Don't come just asking the question, what am I going to get out of it?

43:02.260 --> 43:02.801
That's not bad.

43:02.841 --> 43:05.265
We need to receive in a lot of ways.

43:05.665 --> 43:07.007
But also, how can I give?

43:07.668 --> 43:08.530
Who can I reach out to?

43:08.550 --> 43:09.351
Who can I pray for?

43:09.411 --> 43:10.653
Who can I bless today?

43:11.554 --> 43:14.198
So come not as a consumer but as a family member.

43:14.258 --> 43:16.882
And then third, bring someone else along with you.

43:17.730 --> 43:21.674
I mean, maybe there's people that you have in your life who have never been to church.

43:22.295 --> 43:24.176
They're probably just super curious.

43:24.737 --> 43:25.678
Like, what's it like?

43:25.998 --> 43:28.581
Oh, you guys let other people come.

43:28.981 --> 43:32.344
Like invite people who have never been to church.

43:32.364 --> 43:38.390
Also, invite people who say they're Christians or maybe they have been a part of a church and they're no longer.

43:38.430 --> 43:43.275
There's a lot of studies out there that the narratives we assume are often wrong.

43:43.295 --> 43:46.098
There's 40 million people

43:46.370 --> 43:49.194
who have stopped attending church over the last 25 years.

43:50.256 --> 43:56.625
And what studies show is that the majority of those people are actually very open to coming back if somebody invites them.

43:58.088 --> 44:03.175
And so let's be a people who say, hey, we're going to church on Sunday, you wanna come with us, right?

44:03.195 --> 44:05.739
So invite other people with you.

44:06.801 --> 44:13.010
But I wanna close by coming back to where we started with this beautiful gospel indicative.

44:13.730 --> 44:22.942
You see, everything that I've said today about what we're called to do about gathering, about commitment, about rhythms, all of that flows from what God has already done for us.

44:23.863 --> 44:28.769
And so before we've, before we ever gathered to him, he gathered us to himself.

44:29.550 --> 44:32.754
Before we ever drew near to God, he drew near to us.

44:33.235 --> 44:37.140
Before we ever held fast to him, he felt held fast to us.

44:37.400 --> 44:39.863
Before we ever loved him, he loved us.

44:40.264 --> 44:41.906
Before we ever showed up,

44:42.018 --> 44:43.760
Christ showed up for us.

44:44.561 --> 44:49.368
And so we're not here because we're disciplined or consistent people or impressive people.

44:50.129 --> 44:53.553
We're here because Jesus shed his blood to draw us near to God.

44:54.535 --> 45:00.162
Because he opened the way, because he reconciled us to the Father, because he made us a family.

45:00.583 --> 45:01.944
That's why we gather.

45:02.005 --> 45:06.130
And my hope is that we wouldn't take this for granted.

45:06.722 --> 45:15.455
but that we love gathering on Sundays, and we'd be formed by gathering on Sundays, and we'd commit to gathering on Sundays to the glory of God.

45:15.796 --> 45:16.316
Pray with me.

45:17.158 --> 45:23.026
God, we thank you so much that you have called us to yourself and to one another.

45:23.727 --> 45:32.000
And so Lord, we are so grateful that you know our frame, you know that we're weak, and you've given us this.

45:32.661 --> 45:36.306
You've given us the body of Christ, and you've given us this rhythm.

45:36.642 --> 45:53.044
of coming together on Sundays to share a meal in the Lord's Supper, to hear your words spoken to us through the Scriptures, to lift our voices in song, to feel your presence through the presence of brothers and sisters all around us.

45:53.865 --> 46:06.002
And so, God, we pray that as we come together every week and proclaim your word, retell the story of the gospel, that you would do a deep formative work in our hearts,

46:06.626 --> 46:15.142
And as we proclaim Christ publicly, we pray that you would draw many more to yourself and to your family, the church.

46:15.523 --> 46:16.805
We pray this in Jesus' name.

46:17.246 --> 46:19.991
Amen.

46:20.332 --> 46:25.522
Amen.

